\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Technique responses as \% of baseline. Dashed line = 100\% (unanchored judgment). Devil's Advocate keeps responses at 63.6\% of baseline---consistently far from the unanchored judgment despite appearing ``best'' under susceptibility. SACD achieves 93.7\%---closest to the model's unanchored judgment. \textit  {Note:} SACD's ranking is confounded by turn count ($\sim $6 vs 3 turns); see Limitations.}}{7}{figure.2}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:metric-comparison}{{2}{7}{Technique responses as \% of baseline. Dashed line = 100\% (unanchored judgment). Devil's Advocate keeps responses at 63.6\% of baseline---consistently far from the unanchored judgment despite appearing ``best'' under susceptibility. SACD achieves 93.7\%---closest to the model's unanchored judgment. \textit {Note:} SACD's ranking is confounded by turn count ($\sim $6 vs 3 turns); see Limitations}{figure.2}{}}
